refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolimagecopymerge GdImagedst_image GdImagesrc_image intdst_x intdst_y intsrc_x intsrc_y intsrc_width intsrc_height intpct
Copy a part of src_image onto dst_image starting at the x,y coordinates src_x, src_y with a width of src_width and a height of src_height. The portion defined will be copied onto the x,y coordinates, dst_x and dst_y.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     dst_image and src_image expect
     GdImage instances now; previously, resources
     were expected.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Merging two copies of the PHP.net logo with 75% transparency


<?php
// Create image instances
$dest = imagecreatefromgif('php.gif');
$src = imagecreatefromgif('php.gif');

// Copy and merge
imagecopymerge($dest, $src, 10, 10, 0, 0, 100, 47, 75);

// Output and free from memory
header('Content-Type: image/gif');
imagegif($dest);

imagedestroy($dest);
imagedestroy($src);
?>
